National police commissioner Gen Fannie Masemola and minister Bheki Cele will on Monday receive a full report on the mass shooting that claimed 15 lives at a tavern in Nomzamo informal settlement in Orlando East, Soweto. After the private briefing at the Orlando police station, a site visit to the crime scene will be conducted. A manhunt is under way for the gunmen who arrived in a Quantum minibus taxi and started shooting randomly at tavern patrons  in the early hours  on Sunday. They were armed with rifles and 9mm pistols.  